                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-15T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 15—9:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1656. It was decided today to ask the International Tin Committee to raise the
                    quota for the third quarter to 100 percent. The Dutch have informally agreed.
                    The Colonial Office points out that any deficit in production in the third
                    quarter can be made up by the mines during the fourth quarter but that the mines
                    have large stocks at the pithead which they are now releasing to the smelters
                    rapidly. The Colonial Office is prepared to request an increase in the fourth
                    quarter, if it later seems desirable or necessary but feels that the releases
                    now envisaged will more than meet the markets requirements and will add over
                    25,000 tons to world stocks. The tin markets of London and Singapore will open
                    on Monday with maximum prices of £230 and £227, respectively.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
